    • performTrade

      public boolean performTrade​(Broker broker)
      This method performs a trade. First, the list of entered coins are checked to proceed to start the trade. If tether and monero prices are as in the Strategy D, then the trade is performed successfully. When a trade is not performed, "fail" message is shown in trading actions' table.
      Specified by:
      performTrade in interface Strategy
      Specified by:
      performTrade in class TradingStrategy
      Parameters:
      broker - The Broker object that is using the trading strategy.
      Returns:
      boolean, returns true if a trade is performed successfully, false otherwise.
